
Chicken and Rice Casserole
1 ½ cups rice
1 ½ - 2 cups of chicken
1 can Cream of Mushroom soup
2 cups water
¼ cup chopped onion
¼ teaspoon pepper

1.  Heat oven to 350 degrees.
2. Grease a 9x13 inch  baking dish. 
3. In a bowl mix together soup, water, rice, onion, peper and cut up chicken pieces.
4. Pour into baking dish and bake covered for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
